==Regath, the Arceuus General Store Owner==
* '''Regath:''' What do you require, traveller? I deal in many things.
* {{topt|quest=No|Let's see what you've got.}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Who are you?}}
* {{topt|quest=No|I don't need anything.}}
* {{topt|Can I ask you about Arceuus?}}
** '''Player:''' Can I ask you about Arceuus?
** '''Regath:''' This city holds knowledge many would deem unsafe to share. Why should I be so trusting to you?
** '''Player:''' Well, I'm a...
** '''Player:''' Uhm...
** '''Player:''' A journalist! Yes, a journalist from the mainland. I want to let the wider world know of how this incredible city works.
** '''Regath:''' Someone willing to share knowledge of our great city to many others?
** '''Regath:''' Very well, then. The rest of the world could certainly do with learning about our great library.
** {{tcond|If the player does not have an enchanted quill:}}
*** {{mes|You require the Enchanted Scroll Veos gave you and an Enchanted Quill before gathering information from the shopkeepers.}}
*** '''Player:''' I was hoping to write this all down but I don't have the correct equipment! I'll be back in a tick!
*** '''Regath:''' You're not a very good journalist if you forget your equipment. Very well, then. I'll await your return.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has an enchanted quill:}}
*** {{topt|So what exactly is it the people Arceuus bring to Great Kourend?}}
**** '''Player:''' So what exactly is it the people Arceuus bring to Great Kourend?
**** '''Regath:''' Arceuus is filled with literary and magical scholars. Lead by the great Trobin Arceuus. As a leader, he assists in pushing the limit of our knowledge surrounding magical abilities, souls and the crafting of runic energy.
**** '''Regath:''' He cares not for petty control, focusing instead on the expansion of knowledge within Great Kourend.
**** {{tact|previous}}
*** {{topt|What is there to do in Arceuus?}}
**** '''Player:''' What is there to do in Arceuus?
**** '''Regath:''' Our library is something to behond{{sic}}, but the millennia of knowledge found there; runic, magical and religious, are but small findings compared to the power of the Dark Altar.
**** '''Regath:''' Through its power, we have great knowledge on life and death. This knowledge could be yours as well.
**** '''Player:''' {{overhead|ARGH!}}
**** {{tbox|pic=Enchanted scroll detail.png|pic2=Enchanted quill detail.png|Your quill and scroll glow, causing a seething pain to run through your hand and arm.}}
**** '''Regath:''' What is the matter, journalist?
**** '''Player:''' I... I don't know.
**** '''Player:''' I must have caught my finger with the quill. Apologies; please continue.
**** '''Regath:''' Very well. As mentioned, rewards on offer within our city are priceless. The sharing of our magical research is but child's play compared to the knowledge of Blood and Soul runecrafting.
**** {{tcond|If Regath was not the last general store owner you talked to:}}
***** {{tbox|pic=Enchanted scroll detail.png|pic2=Enchanted quill detail.png|You jot down all of the information Regath had to say about Arceuus.}}
**** {{tcond|If Regath was the last general store owner you talked to:}}
***** {{tbox|As you jot down the final information on Arceuus, you hear a mysterious whisper in your ear. 'Return to Veos...'}}
**** '''Player:''' Thanks for your help!
**** '''Regath:''' You're welcome. Spread the word of this great city with the new knowledge you have gained, and perhaps be more careful with how you hold your scroll in the future...
**** {{tact|end}}

